      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can tell you that a small reduction in dose is not a standard approach. In fact, the American Heart Association recommends that patients on warfarin not attempt to adjust their dose without medical supervision. Reducing the dose without monitoring can lead to increased risk of thrombosis or bleeding. A more common approach would be to work with your doctor to gradually decrease the dose over time, typically in 0.5-1mg increments, while closely monitoring your INR levels. I'd recommend discussing this with your doctor, who can provide personalized guidance on a safe and effective tapering schedule.",
